0the%20opening%20day%20of%20the%20UN%20Climate%20Change%20Conference%20(COP29)%20here%2C%20the%20January-September%20global%20mean%20surface%20temperature%20was%201.54%20degrees%20Celsius%20above%20pre-industrial%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20alarming%20surge%2C%20driven%20by%20an%20intense%20El%20Nino%20event%20and%20rising%20greenhouse%20gas%20concentrations%2C%20marks%20a%20critical%20threshold%20for%20climate%20change%20impacts%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20titled%20%26quot%3BState%20of%20the%20Climate%202024%26quot%3B%20highlights%20the%20accelerating%20risks%20posed%20by%20global%20warming%2C%20particularly%20for%20vulnerable%20communities.%20%26quot%3BClimate%20catastrophe%20is%20hammering%20health%2C%20widening%20inequalities%2C%20harming%20sustainable%20development%2C%20and%20rocking%20the%20foundations%20of%20peace%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20UN%20Secretary-General%20Antonio%20Guterres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGuterres%20emphasised%20the%20urgent%20need%20for%20climate%20action%20to%20protect%20those%20most%20affected%20by%20these%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20finding%20of%20the%20report%20is%20the%20unprecedented%20temperature%20increase.%20The%20average%20global%20temperature%20for%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%202024%20exceeded%20the%20pre-industrial%20level%20by%201.54%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20temporarily%20surpassing%20the%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20goal%20set%20in%20the%20Paris%20Agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20long-term%20warming%20remains%20around%201.3%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20experts%20caution%20that%20every%20fraction%20of%20a%20degree%20compounds%20the%20intensity%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%20and%20exacerbates%20climate%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20observation%20is%20the%20surge%20in%20ocean%20heat%20content%2C%20which%20reached%20a%20historic%20high%20in%202023%20and%20shows%20no%20signs%20of%20abating%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOceans%20have%20absorbed%20over%2090%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20extra%20energy%20from%20global%20warming%2C%20a%20trend%20that%20will%20have%20long-term%20implications%20for%20marine%20life%20and%20coastal%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERising%20ocean%20temperatures%20also%20fuel%20extreme%20weather%20patterns%2C%20further%20intensifying%20climate%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESea%20levels%2C%20driven%20by%20thermal%20expansion%20and%20glacier%20melt%2C%20continue%20to%20rise%20at%20a%20rate%20more%20than%20double%20that%20observed%20between%201993%20and%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20rate%20of%20increase%20slightly%20slowed%20in%202024%2C%20the%20WMO%20warns%20that%20sea%20level%20rise%20remains%20a%20grave%20concern%20for%20coastal%20regions%20worldwide.%20This%20trend%20underscores%20the%20need%20for%20coastal%20communities%20to%20strengthen%20resilience%20against%20rising%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WMO%20report%20also%20draws%20attention%20to%20unprecedented%20glacier%20loss%2C%20with%20a%20record%201.2%20metres%20of%20water%20equivalent%20lost%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlaciers%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20for%20example%2C%20lost%20approximately%2010%20per%20cent%20of%20their%20remaining%20volume%20over%20just%20two%20years.%20Such%20rapid%20glacier%20retreat%20impacts%20mountainous%20and%20polar%20regions%2C%20highlighting%20the%20urgency%20for%20climate%20adaptation%20measures%20in%20these%20vulnerable%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExtreme%20weather%20events%20have%20also%20intensified%20globally%2C%20with%20WMO%20attributing%20deadly%20heatwaves%2C%20severe%20floods%2C%20tropical%20cyclones%2C%20and%20persistent%20droughts%20to%20climate%20change.%20These%20events%20have%20led%20to%20economic%20losses%2C%20food%20insecurity%2C%20and%20forced%20migration%2C%20hindering%20sustainable%20development%20and%20causing%20significant%20human%20suffering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20greenhouse%20gas%20concentrations%20reached%20record%20levels%20in%202023%2C%20with%20CO2%20rising%20to%20420%20parts%20per%20million%2C%20marking%20a%2051%20per%20cent%20increase%20from%20pre-industrial%20levels.%20This%20trend%20has%20persisted%20into%202024%2C%20pushing%20atmospheric%20heat%20retention%20higher%20and%20driving%20further%20warming.%20Such%20findings%20underline%20the%20pressing%20need%20to%20curb%20emissions%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20polar%20ice%20regions%20continue%20to%20experience%20dramatic%20changes.%20Antarctic%20sea%20ice%20extent%20in%202024%20was%20the%20second%20lowest%20since%20satellite%20records%20began%2C%20with%20the%20Arctic%20also%20seeing%20near-record%20lows.%20The%20loss%20of%20polar%20ice%20contributes%20to%20global%20warming%20feedback%20loops%2C%20with%20cascading%20effects%20on%20ecosystems%20and%20weather%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWMO%20Secretary-General%20Celeste%20Saulo%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20climate%20adaptation%2C%20particularly%20through%20initiatives%20like%20Early%20Warnings%20for%20All%20(EW4All)%2C%20which%20aim%20to%20protect%20communities%20from%20extreme%20weather%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20this%20initiative%2C%20108%20countries%20now%20report%20having%20a%20Multi-Hazard%20Early%20Warning%20System%2C%20a%20significant%20step%20towards%20enhancing%20resilience%20in%20vulnerable%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WMO's%20findings%20underscore%20the%20urgency%20of%20reducing%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20and%20implementing%20effective%20climate%20policies.%20In%20response%2C%20a%20team%20of%20international%20experts%20has%20been%20convened%20to%20track%20and%20communicate%20climate%20goals%20relative%20to%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20and%20guide%20policymakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731348300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%